cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.BIO, cs.CV 

This paper involves the development of a neural network technique to learn concepts from electroencephalograms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of statistical and spectral features to classify EEG segments, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of EEG data from newborns, which suggests a possible fit with cs.BIO (Computational Biology) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
